parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel display can cause the driver to be unaware of critical vehicle information, such as fuel level, oil life, and odometer reading, which can lead to safety issues, such as running out of fuel or ignoring important maintenance warnings.
symptoms: The instrument panel display goes blank or becomes garbled and unreadable
the display fails to show fuel level
oil life
or odometer reading
the display is intermittently available
the display is distorted or shows all text at once.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starting system can cause the vehicle to not start or start with difficulty, which can leave the driver stranded or cause accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle won't start
the vehicle starts with cranking
the vehicle requires extended cranking to start
the vehicle has difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality, as the vehicle's safety features are compromised.
symptoms: Airbag warning light indicates malfunction
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
despite meeting the deployment criteria
resulting in potential injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: False Activation of Automatic Emergency Braking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the automatic emergency braking system can cause sudden and unexpected braking, which can lead to accidents, especially in busy traffic conditions.
symptoms: The automatic emergency braking system engages without any objects or vehicles nearby
the brake warning light flashes and beeps
the brakes lock up while driving
the system activates in normal driving conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Activation of Forward Emergency Collision Detection System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the forward emergency collision detection system can cause the vehicle to suddenly and unexpectedly brake, which can lead to accidents, including rear-end collisions, and potentially cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly and unexpectedly brakes
the ABS system engages
the vehicle comes to an abrupt stop
no obstacles or vehicles are present in front of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Front End Vibration when Applying Brakes at Highway Speeds
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive vibration of the front end when applying the brakes at highway speeds can cause loss of control, reduced braking performance, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents and potentially cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle vibrates excessively when applying the brakes at highway speeds
the vibration feels like it is coming from the disk brakes on the front wheels.
